### Configure Supabase Storage Client to Throw Errors (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase-js/blob/master/packages/core/storage-js/README.md

This snippet demonstrates how to configure the Supabase Storage client to throw exceptions on API errors instead of returning an error object. It shows a `try...catch` block to handle `StorageApiError` instances, allowing for more traditional error handling patterns.

```typescript
const analytics = storageClient.analytics
analytics.throwOnError()

try {
  const { data } = await analytics.createBucket('my-bucket')
  // data is guaranteed to be present
  console.log('Success:', data)
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof StorageApiError) {
    console.error('API Error:', error.statusCode, error.message)
  }
}
```

