### Set Up Global Error and Unhandled Promise Rejection Handlers

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase-js/blob/master/packages/core/supabase-js/test/integration/node-browser/index.html

This code snippet attaches event listeners to the global 'window' object to catch and log unhandled errors and promise rejections. It provides detailed diagnostic information, such as the error message, source file, line number, or the reason for rejection, facilitating debugging in a browser environment.

```javascript
// Add global error handler
window.addEventListener('error', (event) => {
  log('Global error: ' + event.message)
  log('Error source: ' + event.filename + ':' + event.lineno)
})
// Add unhandled promise rejection handler
window.addEventListener('unhandledrejection', (event) => {
  log('Unhandled promise rejection: ' + event.reason)
})
```

