### Invoke Supabase Edge Function with JSON Body (JavaScript)

Source: https://context7.com/supabase/supabase-js/llms.txt

Calls a Supabase Edge Function, passing a JSON object as the request body and optional custom headers. This example includes basic error handling and logs the function's response or any encountered errors.

```javascript
const { data, error } = await functions.invoke('hello-world', {
  body: {
    name: 'Alice',
    message: 'Hello from client'
  },
  headers: {
    'x-custom-header': 'custom-value'
  }
})

if (error) {
  console.error('Function error:', error.message)
} else {
  console.log('Function response:', data)
}
```

